 and extralegal repression of publication can also become the stuff of news about news makers. When the subjects of news inhabit multiple participant roles in the unfolding of public events, when the very technologies of recording and circulating events themselves become news, the act of representing a political event becomes difficult to disentangle from that of participating in it. This, Cody argues, is the crisis of contemporary news making: the news can no longer claim exteriority to the world on which it reports.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDigital mediaxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aJournalismxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aMass mediaxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  amedia, India, journalism, democracy, Tamil, event, anthropology, popular sovereignty, law, news.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226824741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226824741/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles